	"packageName": "@anvilkit/ir",
	"readme": [
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "# @anvilkit/ir\n\nHeadless transforms that turn Puck "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`Data`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " into the normalized\n["
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`PageIR`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "]("
		},
		{
			"kind": "relative-link",
			"text": "../core/src/types/ir.ts",
			"target": 2
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ") shape every Anvilkit export\nformat consumes. "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`@anvilkit/ir`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " is the first of three headless\nruntime packages ("
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`ir`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ", "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`schema`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ", "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`validator`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ") and sits directly\nabove "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`@anvilkit/utils`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " in the dependency graph — it imports zero\nReact, no DOM, and no other "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`@anvilkit/*`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " runtime.\n\n> **Alpha status (0.1.x).** The four public exports are implemented\n> and covered by round-trip, canonical-form, and snapshot tests.\n> The IR shape is **frozen at end of M1** — any change requires a\n> Core minor bump and an "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`ir_shape_changed`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " changeset.\n\n## Install\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "```bash\npnpm add @anvilkit/ir @puckeditor/core\n```"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n## Quickstart\n\n"
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "```ts\nimport { puckDataToIR, irToPuckData } from \"@anvilkit/ir\";\nimport type { Config, Data } from \"@puckeditor/core\";\n\ndeclare const config: Config;\ndeclare const data: Data;\n\n// Normalize Puck data into the IR shape exporters consume.\nconst ir = puckDataToIR(data, config);\n\n// Rebuild the original Puck data from an IR document.\nconst roundTripped = irToPuckData(ir);\n```"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "\n\n## Phase 3 references\n\nSee the [Phase 3 plan]("
		},
		{
			"kind": "relative-link",
			"text": "../../docs/plans/phase-3-export-ai-pipeline-plan.md",
			"target": 3
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ")\n("
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`M1 — @anvilkit/ir`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ") and the\n[architecture package catalog]("
		},
		{
			"kind": "relative-link",
			"text": "../../docs/ai-context/anvilkit-architecture.md",
			"target": 4
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ")\n("
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`§7 — @anvilkit/ir [Planned]`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ") for the IR contract, dependency\ndirection, and release expectations.\n\n## Public API\n\n| Export           | Signature                                                          | Purpose                                                                                              |\n| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`puckDataToIR`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "   | "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`(data: Data, config: Config) => PageIR`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "                           | Normalize a Puck document into a JSON-serializable "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`PageIR`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ".                                         |\n| "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`irToPuckData`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "   | "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`(ir: PageIR) => Data`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "                                             | Reverse of "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`puckDataToIR`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " — used for round-trip tests and the AI copilot's "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`setData`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " dispatch.       |\n| "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`collectAssets`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "  | "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`(node: PageIRNode) => readonly PageIRAsset[]`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "                     | Walk a sub-tree and collect every referenced asset, deduplicated.                                    |\n| "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`identifySlots`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "  | "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`(config: Config) => Map<string, readonly string[]>`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "               | Inspect a Puck "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`Config`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " and return the slot-field keys declared on each component.                   |\n\n## Peer dependencies\n\n| Package | Version |\n| ------- | ------- |\n| "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`@puckeditor/core`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " | "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`^0.21.0`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " |\n\n## Dependency contract\n\n| Allowed                       | Forbidden                                                               |\n| ----------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`@anvilkit/utils`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " (runtime)   | "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`@anvilkit/schema`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ", "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`@anvilkit/validator`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ", "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`@anvilkit/core`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " runtime     |\n| "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`@puckeditor/core`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " (peer, types-only) | React, ReactDOM, any plugin package, any DOM API                |\n\nCI enforces these with "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`madge --circular`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ", "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`check:react-free-runtime`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ",\nand "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`check:peer-deps`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " gates (land in "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`phase3-015`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "). See\n[Phase 3 plan §8]("
		},
		{
			"kind": "relative-link",
			"text": "../../docs/plans/phase-3-export-ai-pipeline-plan.md",
			"target": 3
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ")\nand the [architecture doc §8 L441-L487]("
		},
		{
			"kind": "relative-link",
			"text": "../../docs/ai-context/anvilkit-architecture.md",
			"target": 4
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ")\nfor the full rationale.\n\n## Snapshots\n\nThe ["
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`src/__tests__/__snapshots__/`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": "]("
		},
		{
			"kind": "relative-link",
			"text": "src/__tests__/__snapshots__/",
			"target": 5
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ") directory\ncontains 9 committed "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`.snap.ts`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " files — one for each demo component. Each\nfile exports a typed "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`PageIR`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " constant that compiles under the package's\nown TypeScript config, so any IR shape drift surfaces as both a test failure\n**and** a type error.\n\nSnapshot tests run as part of "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`pnpm --filter @anvilkit/ir test`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ". They\nassert that "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`puckDataToIR(fixture, config)`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " produces output structurally\nequal to the committed snapshot, and that two consecutive runs produce\nbyte-identical output (determinism).\n\n### IR shape freeze rule\n\nThe "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`PageIR`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " shape is **frozen at end of M1**. After this milestone:\n\n- Any change to "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`PageIR`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ", "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`PageIRNode`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ", "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`PageIRAsset`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": ", or\n  "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`PageIRMetadata`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " requires a **Core minor bump**.\n- The PR must include an "
		},
		{
			"kind": "code",
			"text": "`ir_shape_changed`"
		},
		{
			"kind": "text",
			"text": " changeset.\n- All 9 snapshot files must be regenerated and re-committed.\n\nThis policy ensures downstream exporters and the AI copilot plugin can\npin against a stable contract."
		}
	],
